raph -->\n<p>This easy online bond service allows you to purchase limits from $5,000 to $100,000 instantly.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"faq-does\">Does it matter how many employees I have?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes.  Janitorial Service Bonds premium is based on the number of employees the business has.  With this easy online bond service you\'ll only have to let us know if you have have or less employees or six or more employees.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"faq-how\">How are renewals handled?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Janitorial Service Bonds are continuous bonds.  This simply means that as long as you pay the renewal premium the bond is active.  The only other time a document will be issued by the carrier would be if the bond was cancelled.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The renewal process is even simpler than purchasing the policy.  You can choose the auto pay option which means that your payment method will be billed automatically or you can just simply pay the renewal invoice online when you receive the renewal email.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"faq-can\">Can a Janitorial Service Bond be cancelled?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes.  Bonds can be cancelled if you are closing the business or decide that you no longer want the coverage.  If you would like to cancel a bond purchased through our office please reach out to us at (305)470-8500 or email us at info@dopazo.com so that we can discuss the signatures needed to request cancellation.  Don\'t worry this process is all done electronically so it will be quick and simple just like purchasing the bond.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"faq-whatif\">What if I need limits higher than $100,000?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading --